e_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_deb41abf-e406-4d55-b1dc-0564d721f514_1000x.jpg?v=1691681389 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_providing_care_certificate_training_is_important_for_health_and_social_care_managers_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_deb41abf-e406-4d55-b1dc-0564d721f514_500x.jpg?v=1691681389 320w" width="2453" height="1637" alt="Why providing care certificate training is important for health and social care managers - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Why providing care certificate training is important for health and social care managers - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-15_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-2c5a" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-eSxRXt eFcmyr pf-16_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-jNHqnW kAyuLL"><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-17_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fvpsdx eVTiRY pf-18_"><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-19_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-21_">The Care Certificate, developed collaboratively by Health Education England, Skills for Care, and Skills for Health, is an essential set of standards that health and social care workers must adhere to in their daily work. In this blog, we will discuss why <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/train-the-trainer-courses-and-qualifications" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 138, 0);"><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">trainers</span></span></i></a> should prioritise teaching the care certificate for induction training, highlighting its importance in ensuring compassionate, safe, and high-quality care and support.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-24_">The need for the care certificate</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_need_for_the_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691672149" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_need_for_the_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691672149 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_need_for_the_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1691672149 320w" width="1643" height="1088" alt="The need for the care certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The need for the care certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-25_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-28_">The care certificate was introduced as a direct response to The Cavendish Review, conducted in the wake of reports of abuse and neglect at Mid Staffordshire NHS Trust. It serves as a means to prevent such incidents from recurring by equipping workers with the necessary skills, knowledge, and behaviours to deliver quality care. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-31_">A foundation for career progression </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_foundation_for_career_progression_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_82516afe-a0b0-4fee-b40b-1958cd06b4bc.jpg?v=1691678843" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_foundation_for_career_progression_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_82516afe-a0b0-4fee-b40b-1958cd06b4bc.jpg?v=1691678843 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_foundation_for_career_progression_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_82516afe-a0b0-4fee-b40b-1958cd06b4bc_500x.jpg?v=1691678843 320w" width="2318" height="1568" alt="A foundation for career progression - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="A foundation for career progression - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-32_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-35_">While the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/care-certificate-train-the-trainer-trainer-pack-cpduk-accredited?variant=31839814582341" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">care certificate</span></i></a> is a minimum requirement for all health and social care workers, it also acts as a solid foundation on which individuals can further develop their knowledge and skills throughout their career progression. By completing the care certificate, workers are equipped with the fundamental skills needed to deliver quality care, laying the groundwork for ongoing professional growth and development. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-38_">Care quality commission expectations</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Care_quality_commission_expectations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691672899" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Care_quality_commission_expectations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691672899 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Care_quality_commission_expectations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1691672899 320w" width="1920" height="1280" alt="Care quality commission expectations - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Care quality commission expectations - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-39_"/><p class="sc-ljMRFG jiRhOP pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-42_">Although there is no legal requirement to complete the care certificate, care employers are expected by the Care Quality Commission (CQC) to deliver the certificate or provide equivalent training that enables staff to meet the required standards. This expectation underscores the importance of ensuring that staff are equipped with the necessary skills and knowledge to provide compassionate, safe, and high-quality care.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-45_">Relevant for various roles</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Relevant_for_various_roles_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_d2f450cf-7a34-44ae-b3f5-2cae21ea9dcb.jpg?v=1691681606" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Relevant_for_various_roles_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_d2f450cf-7a34-44ae-b3f5-2cae21ea9dcb.jpg?v=1691681606 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Relevant_for_various_roles_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_d2f450cf-7a34-44ae-b3f5-2cae21ea9dcb_500x.jpg?v=1691681606 320w" width="2240" height="1493" alt="Relevant for various roles - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Relevant for various roles - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-46_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-47_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The care certificate is particularly relevant for workers in healthcare and adult social care settings. This includes healthcare support workers, healthcare assistants, assistant practitioners, and any individuals providing support to clinical roles that involve direct contact with patients. In adult social care, workers in various settings, such as residential homes, nursing homes, domiciliary care, and hospices, benefit from the training provided by the Care Certificate. While the care certificate is primarily aimed at these specific roles, employers have the flexibility to determine whether any other staff groups, such as cleaners and maintenance within their organisation, would benefit from the standardised training.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-51_">Duration and standards</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Duration_and_standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691673794" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Duration_and_standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691673794 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Duration_and_standards_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1691673794 320w" width="2000" height="1500" alt="Duration and standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Duration and standards - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-52_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-53_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To ensure that staff members are adequately trained, completing the care certificate typically takes around 12 weeks for a full-time staff member. This timeframe allows for the necessary learning and assessment to occur while the individual is on the job. <br><br><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/dr-richard-dune/we-are-endorsed-by-skills-for-care" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Skills for Care</span></i></a> outlines there are fifteen minimum standards that must be completed involving knowledge learning, practical skills, and workplace assessments. Completion of all standards is required to attain the Care Certificate. These minimum standards are:</p><div class="sc-efQSVx kdrjec pf-278_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fvpsdx eVTiRY pf-276_"><ul style="--text-indent:px;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dYtuZ bTisNR pf-55_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-56_">Understand your role</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-58_">Your personal development</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-60_">Duty of care</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-62_">Equality and diversity</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-64_">Work in a person-centred way       </li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-66_">Communication</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-68_">Privacy and dignity</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-70_">Fluids and nutrition</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fvpsdx eVTiRY pf-277_"><ul style="--text-indent:px;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dYtuZ bTisNR pf-327_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-314_">9.&nbsp;Awareness of mental health, dementia and learning disabilities</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-316_">10.&nbsp;Safeguarding adults</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-318_">11.&nbsp;Safeguarding children</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-320_">12.&nbsp;Basic life support</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-322_">13.&nbsp;Health and safety</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-324_">14.&nbsp;Handling information</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAWBJg ciQrUe pf-326_">15.&nbsp;Infection prevention and control.</li></ul></div></div></div><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-86_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">It is pivotal for trainers to ensure that each standard is fully completed and assessed before workers can proceed to work unsupervised.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-88_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-90_">Delivering your care certificate training</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Delivering_your_care_certificate_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691674142" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Delivering_your_care_certificate_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691674142 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Delivering_your_care_certificate_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1691674142 320w" width="2500" height="1667" alt="Delivering your care certificate training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Delivering your care certificate training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jOxtWs ffIUiZ pf-91_"/><p class="sc-ehCJOs iphVAH pf-92_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">If you're thinking about becoming an induction trainer, our <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/train-the-trainer-courses-and-qualifications" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">train-the-trainer</span></i></a> packages can equip you with the necessary skills to create a fully compliant team of care staff. Becoming an in-house trainer has numerous benefits, such as aiding in employee retention and providing a cost-effective approach. Our courses can be accessed through our user-friendly learning management system (LMS), which offers full reporting capabilities and can be accessed from any device, anywhere and anytime.<br><br>Additionally, we offer a complete suite of software that will help you manage your induction training and increase the efficiency of your operations. With <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/complyplus-cqc-compliance-system" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">ComplyPlus CQC Compliance Software</span></i></a>, you'll effortlessly manage your training and compliance documents. Keep all of your HR files in one central place and track your staff's progress with ease. The software will notify you when it's time for training modules to be completed, and you'll have access to reporting figures for your review. The accredited learning management system gives you the necessary tools to improve your compliance rating.<br> <br><a href="https://share.hsforms.com/1jl1hTOkJTb6-wUrjeFdhwg2152b" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Contact us</span></i></a> for more information about the compliance management solutions we offer.</p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-eJwWfJ hSzDKM pf-94_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eZKLwX jcZVJU pf-96_">Conclusion</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_providing_care_certificate_training_is_important_for_health_and_social_care_managers_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691674576" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_providing_care_certificate_training_is_important_for_health_and_social_care_managers_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1691674576 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_providing_care_certificate_training_is_important_for_health_and_social_care_managers_-_Conclusion_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1691674576 320w" width="1512" height="1088" alt="Why providing care certificate training is important for health and social care managers - Conclusion - The Mandatory Trai